sentences: Reuben "Ruby" Braff (March 16, 1927 – February 9, 2003) was an American jazz trumpeter and cornetist.
He began playing in local clubs in the 1940s.
In 1949, he was hired to play with the Edmond Hall Orchestra at the Savoy Cafe of Boston.
He relocated to New York in 1953 where he was much in demand for band dates and recordings.
He resided in Harwich, Massachusetts and died of complications from emphysema, heart failure, and glaucoma on February 9, 2003, in Chatham, Massachusetts.
